Subject: Re: [T2] Re: diagnostic plug - can one measure compression 

On Sat, 11 Jun 2005, Stephen wrote:

> Something I forgot to mention - I have acquired various bits of paper
> from 1973, and they are pretty consistent that the compression was
> measured using the diagnostic socket. This seems to rule out measuring
> the starter motor current, unless the computer connection also included
> a clamp style ammeter.


Current could be measured via the voltage drop in the battery cables, if
the resistance of the battery cables was known.  More likely, they were
simply comparing the battery voltage as each piston reached TDC and
looking for one that didn't drop as far.

George
